title: China, Germany to operate space experiments on Shenzhou-8

cleanContent: JIUQUAN, Oct. 31 (Xinhua) -- A China manned space program spokesperson said here Monday that Chinese and German scientists are going to operate 17 space experiments on life science on the Chinese spacecraft Shenzhou-8.The unmanned spacecraft Shenzhou-8 is scheduled to be launched at 5:58 a.m. Tuesday and dock with China's first space lab module, Tiangong-1, spokeswoman Wu Ping said at a press briefing.																																																																								|  |
